    <h2>Pre-open recovery checklist</h2>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Write down the exact model:</strong> handheld names are reused across generations, special editions, and storage tiers.</li>
      <li><strong>Decide clone vs clean recovery:</strong> cloning needs an enclosure; clean recovery needs manufacturer recovery media, Windows setup, drivers, launcher logins, and patience.</li>
      <li><strong>Back up non-cloud data:</strong> screenshots, mod folders, emulator directories where legal, offline saves, documents, and launcher-specific files.</li>
      <li><strong>Check BitLocker/device encryption:</strong> make sure you can unlock or recover Windows if encryption is enabled.</li>
      <li><strong>Use the right tools:</strong> precision screwdriver kit, pry tool if recommended by a real repair guide, screw tray, clean desk, and no rushing.</li>
      <li><strong>Keep the original SSD:</strong> do not wipe or sell it until the new drive has survived several boot cycles, updates, and game launches.</li>
    </ol>

